{'type': {'name': 'type/page'}, 'name': 'about/schema', 'd': {'body': 'Please see Karen Coyle\'s recent [notes](http://www.kcoyle.net/temp/PharosSchema+kc.html) on the schema.\r\n\r\nFollowing is a python datastructure representing the field-schema for bibliographic items in ThingDB.  Where the `count` attribute is not specified, its value is `\'single\'`.  The types `string`, `text`, `url` (and perhaps `date`) may all be stored as "strings" in ThingDB, but the distinction here may help to render those strings appropriately in the UI.\r\n\r\n        {\r\n\r\n                \'author\':\r\n                {\r\n                        \'name\': { \'type\': \'string\' },\r\n                        \'birth_date\': { \'type\': \'date\' },\r\n                        \'death_date\': { \'type\': \'date\' },\r\n                        \'bio\': { \'type\': \'text\' },\r\n                },\r\n\r\n                \'edition\':\r\n                {\r\n                        \'source_name\': { \'type\': \'string\' },\r\n                        \'source_record_pos\': { \'type\': \'int\' },\r\n                        \'authors\': { \'type\': \'id-ref\', \'count\': \'multiple\' },\r\n                        \'contributions\': { \'type\': \'string\', \'count\': \'multiple\' },\r\n                        \'title\': { \'type\': \'string\' },\r\n                        \'bio\': { \'type\': \'text\' },\r\n                        \'title_prefix_len\': { \'type\': \'int\', \'description\': \'number of chars to skip for sorting\' },\r\n                        \'edition\': { \'type\': \'string\', \'description\': \'information about this edition\' },\r\n                        \'subject\': { \'type\': \'string\', \'count\': \'multiple\' },\r\n                        \'BISAC_subject_categories\': { \'type\': \'string\', \'description\': \'see http://www.bisg.org/standards/bisac_subject/index.html\' },\r\n                        \'publisher\': { \'type\': \'string\' },\r\n                    