r final site so that people can get the metadata in an XML format? Also, it may be handy to consider the use case of \'citation bookmarking\' software such as Endnote and RefWorks and provide exporting functionality accordingly.\r\n\r\n> Commented by Ben O\'Steen - Tue 17 Jul\r\n\r\n>I notice that there is are no fields for volume/issue/date information for serials, nor is there any way to show relationships among serial parts .  There also doesn\'t seem to be a field for ISSN.  Is this schema only for monographs, and you are developing a separate one for serials and other multi-part items, or is this merely a first draft?  One great thing about developing a new schema is the opportunity to address the expression of parent-child relationships -- something that current schemas do poorly or not at all.\r\n>Commented by Keri Thompson - Tue 17 Jul', 'title': 'Schema'}}